title: Mount Seebeck
text: Mount Seebeck () is a <a href="mountain">mountain</a> standing directly at the head of <a href="Roe%20Glacier">Roe Glacier</a> in the <a href="Tapley%20Mountains">Tapley Mountains</a>, <a href="Queen%20Maud%20Mountains">Queen Maud Mountains</a>. Mapped by <a href="United%20States%20Geological%20Survey">United States Geological Survey</a> (USGS) from surveys and <a href="U.S.%20Navy">U.S. Navy</a> air photos, 1960–64. Named by <a href="Advisory%20Committee%20on%20Antarctic%20Names">Advisory Committee on Antarctic Names</a> (US-ACAN) for <a href="Richard%20L.%20Seebeck">Richard L. Seebeck</a>, station engineer at <a href="McMurdo%20Station">McMurdo Station</a>, winter party, 1962.
